10 objectives, and an implementation plan as described in subsection (10) to improve the basic system of free,
11 quality, public elementary and secondary schools.
12 (2) In conducting the study, the commission may:
13 (a) review the work of previous studies and commissions;
14 (b) consider recommendations and topics provided by other interim or standing legislative
15 committees, the board of public education, the office of public instruction, the governor's office, private
16 organizations, professional educators, school trustees, and members of the public;
17 (c) review how the state's education funding policy has evolved as a result of litigation;
18 (d) seek input from representatives from the board of public education, the office of public
19 instruction, the governor's office, private organizations, professional educators, school trustees, and members
20 of the public;
21 (e) consider the state's existing and projected financial resources as well as the needs and
22 concerns of Montana taxpayers;
23 (f) authorize research and studies to be conducted by reputable and reliable experts in the public
24 or private sectors; and
25 (g) request research and analysis from the legislative fiscal division, the office of public instruction,
26 the department of revenue, and any other state agency or entity that maintains information or data relevant to
27 the study.
